\title{3.3 The warmest and coldest day of each year}
\author{Alexander Degener}
\date{November 2021}

\begin{document}

\maketitle


\section{Goals}
This part of the project is about finding the hottest and coldest days of each year. The temperature data from a specific region in Sweden shall be read by a program, sorted according to date and then processed to find out when minimum and maximum temperature instances occur.\\
The information produced by processing the data should also produce histograms enabling predictions on when future hottest and coldest days might occur. A histograms showing instances of hottest and coldest days at the same time should also be produced.\\
Additionally, the program should be able to find the hottest and coldest temperatures every day of any year. These temperatures should then be plotted in histograms individually as well as in the same histogram, in that way illustrating the maximum temperature difference each day of any year.

\\
