\\
\section{Approach}
The cleaned data-file for Karlstad was read by a program one line at a time. One part of each line was saved in a list of dates and one in a list of temperatures for each year.\\
When one year had been looped through the temperatures of each day were compared and stored in lists for minimi temperature and maxima temperature.\\
Appropriate lists were made for single years and all years respectively, containing temperatures or days of hottest or coldest temperatures.\\
The values of the lists were then plotted as individual histograms and also using two plots in the same histograms.


\section{Prediction}
Based on the histogram in figure 1, the coldest day during the year should be very likely to occur around the first week of January, and the hottest day around the middle of July.

